    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect minimum buffer length check in encode_pdn_address\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_pdn_address` function was using a fixed minimum buffer length of 7 bytes regardless of whether an IEI was present. This caused the function to incorrectly fail when IEI=0 and only 6 bytes were provided, since 6 bytes is sufficient for encoding without IEI (1 byte length + 1 byte type + 4 bytes IPv4 address).\n\nThis fix adjusts the minimum length requirement dynamically based on IEI presence.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/PdnAddress.c`: Added dynamic minimum length calculation that subtracts 1 byte when IEI is not present (iei=0), changing the requirement from 7 bytes to 6 bytes in that case.\n\nWhen calling `encode_pdn_address()` with IEI=0 and a 6-byte buffer, the function previously returned `TLV_ENCODE_BUFFER_TOO_SHORT` even though the buffer was adequate. After this fix, the function correctly processes the request and returns the number of encoded bytes.\n"
}